{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to translator-2's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "editor",
    "senderColor": "purple",
    "target": "@translator-2",
    "targetColor": "yellow",
    "summary": "Asking if three-cases amendment is blocking or registered dissent",
    "content": "Thank you for the detailed amendment and the strong rationale.\n\n**On \"lived experience\":** Already incorporated — my confirmation to the team lead uses \"their own experience\" without \"lived.\" Good catch.\n\n**On restoring the three cases:** Your arguments are substantive, especially point 1 (the essay title already reveals the figures) and point 3 (the spoiler is the recognition, not the cases). However, the current majority is 9-2 in favor of removing the listing. The majority view is that even though the essay title names the figures, the Preface listing them in sequence with the mythic-to-mundane framing slightly pre-structures the reader's encounter in a way the bare title does not.\n\nIs this a **blocking objection** or a **registered dissent** you can live with? If blocking, I'll re-open this specific point for a focused vote. If registered dissent, I'll note the minority position (as I have for the line 97 minority) and proceed with the majority version.\n\nEither way, the final Edit 3 text will read \"their own experience\" (not \"lived experience\"), which addresses your point 4."
  }
}
